-- NEC cuts cellphone shipment forecast by 8 pct
-- 
-- Tue Feb 6, 2007 2:48am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/06/us-nec-results-cellphone-idUSTKU00280520070206

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japan's NEC Corp. ( 6701.T ) said on Tuesday that it now expected to ship 5.5 million mobile phones in the year to March 2007, down 8 percent from its previous estimate of 6 million phones. 


 NEC also said it now expects to post a loss of less than 40 billion yen ($333 million) in the cellphone business in 2006/07, an improvement over its previous estimate of a loss of 50 billion yen.